narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Take it if you are interested in poetry. If you are not, this course will kill you.
I would recommend this class for everyone because I think it is imperative for everyone to be able to appreciate and understand poetry written in the English language.

Well, if you're an English major, you'll definitely want to take 125. Professor Cornelius is great, and has an especially thorough knowledge of Chaucer and Spenser. Plus, the class will give you a lot of experience writing literary analysis papers -- and the materials you read will give you a really thorough grounding in English literature. Take it!
